      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ يَحُجُّ عَنْ أَبِيهِ أَ يَتَمَتَّعُ قَالَ «نَعَمْ اَلْمُتْعَةُ لَهُ وَ اَلْحَجُّ عَنْ أَبِيهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2932 - Ja'far ibn Bashir narrated from Al-'Ala', from Muhammad ibn Muslim, from Abu Ja'far (as), who said:\nI asked him about a man who performs Hajj on behalf of his father. Should he perform Tamattu‘ (Umrah and Hajj combined)?\nImam (as) said: \"Yes, the Tamattu‘ is for him, and the Hajj is on behalf of his father.\""
        ]
      }
    },
